comments.body:
{quote}
 When node label expression is empty string, only default partition without non-exclusive allocation is used,
when node label expression is null, only it allowed non-exclusive allocation.
{quote}
I am concerned that this change does not conform to the intent of the requirements of the partition label feature.
Exclusivity and non-exclusivity are associated with a partition when it is created. Queues can be associated with these partitions and the default behavior in those queues is defined by the queue's partition labels and their attributes. I feel that it is improper to change the behavior based on whether or not the user has specified an empty string or a null.

